name: CD - Whatever Happened To Rock'n'Roll?
description:
12 track CD Released March 2011 on Bad Soul Records.

1. Whatever Happened To Rock'n'Roll?
2. Hurricane.
3. Chet Head.
4. I'd Like To See You Naked.
5. Dirty Robber.
6. I'm A Red Blooded Boy.
7. Teenage Kicks.
8. You're A Long Time Dead.
9. Chick Berry.
10. I Don't Think I Like You Anymore.
11. Another Attack.
12. Paint It Black.

£8.99 price includes shipping Worlwide.

“Whatever happened to Rock and Roll?”… stop wasting your time on the $1000 question, the answer is crystal clear! The Mojokings took over!”...billybop.be, May 2011

“Whatever happened to rock ‘n’ roll?” is the title of the new album by Mojokings. If that is a question, the answer would be: Mojokings are what happened to rock and roll. A perfect combination of garage, trash, psycho-rockabilly and hard rock and roll…. Must have for anyone, who considers themselves rock and roll (not for the weak hearted)”…psycho.rockabilly-online.com, March 2011

“This album takes me back to the 80s and nights at The Klubfoot for all the right reasons, one big one being that rather than following the crowd The MojoKings have carved out their own direction in this field. Point your browser towards http://www.mojokings.com to learn where to buy a copy ASAP, - you won’t regret it! “…Scootering Magazine, Recommended Listening May 2011
